Engineering in Canada: Top Universities, Eligibility, Courses, Application Process

  • 1842 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Apr 13,2023 05:39 PM IST

Engineering is a rewarding career which involves science and technology to design and build machines. Engineering in Canada offers excellent opportunities for international students in universities with top QS World Rankings. Read the blog to know about popular universities, eligibility, courses, application processes and more.

Canada remains at the top spot in pursuing post secondary education among international students and while the country offers a wide range of program options, engineering in Canada continues to be a popular choice. The country is home to world-renowned engineering universities, out of which 5 universities are ranked in the top 150 list of QS World University Rankings 2023. Engineering in itself is a prestigious and promising career option. It involves concepts of mathematics, science and technology to design and build machines.

This blog includes detailed knowledge of engineering in Canada, including engineering programs, their eligibility criteria, specializations offered in top universities and application processes.

Top 5 Reasons to Study Engineering in Canada

1.Best Engineering Universities
Engineering institutes in Canada, such as McGill University, the University of Toronto, the University of British Columbia, the University of Alberta and the University of Montreal, are ranked high in the top 150 QS World University Rankings list.
2.Rewarding Career Opportunities  
Canadian degree is held high globally, which offers graduates lucrative employment opportunities. As suggested by a report from engineers in Canada, there is a need to fill 1,00,000 engineering job positions in Canada by 2025 and the demand for engineers continues to grow.
3.Lower Educational Costs
Canada provides high quality education using modern teaching methods at lower tuition fee than other countries like USA or UK. Moreover, lower costs of living makes the student life easy.
4.Wide Range of Specializations
Various engineering specializations are available in Canada, from Computer Engineering to Biomedical Engineering to less popular specializations such as Environmental and Agricultural Engineering.
5.International Exposure
Studying abroad allows international students to grow holistically as they interact with people from different cultural backgrounds, learn from their experiences and level up their skills.

Application Process to Apply for Engineering in Canada

Follow the steps below to get admission into engineering programs in Canadian universities and colleges:
•Research and shortlist the institutions of choice and apply according to the field of interest and the university requirements.
•Prepare and attempt for the English Language Proficiency Test (IELTS, TOEFL or PTE)
•Fill out the application forms, pay the application fee and upload the academic transcripts and English Proficiency Test scorecard.
•After enrolling in a program, settle funds and apply for a student visa.

Documents Required to Study in Canada for International Students

Documents given below are required to apply for pursuing engineering in Canada.
•Educational mark sheets and certificates
•English Language Proficiency Test Scores (IELTS, TOEFL, PTE) and GRE
•Valid passport
•Statement of Purpose (SOP)
•Letter of Recommendation
•Resume/CV
•Proof of Funds
•Tuition Fee receipts

FAQ

What are the job prospects of engineering in Canada?

Engineers in Canada have a high employment rate ranging from 87%-89%. Various engineering specializations are –
Electrical Engineers
Civil Engineers
Mechanical Engineers
Software Engineers
Industrial and Manufacturing Engineers

Is a GRE score required for studying engineering in Canada?

A valid GRE score is required to pursue a Masters Degree in Engineering in Canada.

How many intakes are offered in Canada to study Engineering?

Canada offers three intakes - January (winter) intake, September (fall) intake and May (summer/spring) intake. Fall is the most popular intake to study engineering as a variety of programs are available in this intake.

Which English Proficiency Tests are accepted in Canada?

IELTS, TOEFL and PTE Academic are accepted in Canada.

What is the duration of a masters in Engineering in Canada?

The duration of a masters degree in Engineering in Canada is of 2 years.

Which are the most in demand engineering jobs in Canada?

Some of the in-demand engineering jobs in Canada are-
•Electrical Engineers
•Mechanical Engineers
•Chemical Engineers
•Software / IT Engineers
•Civil Engineers
•Aerospace Engineering
